1
00:00:01,168 --> 00:00:03,003
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

2
00:01:00,936 --> 00:01:01,979
(ALARM CLOCK BUZZES)

3
00:01:13,073 --> 00:01:14,575
-Bye.
-See you later.

4
00:02:01,204 --> 00:02:02,247
Bye!

5
00:02:05,459 --> 00:02:07,169
WOMAN: (ON PA)
This is a customer announcement.

6
00:02:07,252 --> 00:02:09,921
The store will be closing
in five minutes. Thank you.

7
00:02:14,468 --> 00:02:15,510
Oi!

8
00:02:36,323 --> 00:02:37,366
(LIFT BELL DINGS)

9
00:02:44,915 --> 00:02:45,957
Wilson?

10
00:02:48,126 --> 00:02:50,003
Wilson, I've got
the lottery money.

11
00:02:51,755 --> 00:02:53,423
Wilson?

12
00:02:53,507 --> 00:02:55,008
-(KNOCKING)
-You there?

13
00:02:57,594 --> 00:03:00,764
Look, I can't hang about
'cause they're closing the shop.

14
00:03:01,932 --> 00:03:03,433
Wilson?

15
00:03:04,101 --> 00:03:05,769
(MUTTERS) Oh, come on.

16
00:03:05,894 --> 00:03:06,937
(CLATTERING)

17
00:03:09,064 --> 00:03:10,107
Hello?

18
00:03:13,735 --> 00:03:15,570
Hello? Wilson, it's Rose.

19
00:03:18,740 --> 00:03:19,783
Hello?

20
00:03:21,576 --> 00:03:22,744
(STAMMERS) Wilson?

21
00:03:42,723 --> 00:03:44,266
(SWITCH CLICKS)

22
00:03:49,312 --> 00:03:50,397
Wilson?

23
00:04:00,157 --> 00:04:01,408
Wilson!

24
00:04:09,499 --> 00:04:10,834
(DOOR SLAMMING)

25
00:04:19,176 --> 00:04:21,011
(MUTTERING)
Oh, you're kidding me!

26
00:04:21,136 --> 00:04:23,013
(CLANKING)

27
00:04:27,309 --> 00:04:29,811
Is that someone
mucking about?

28
00:04:40,113 --> 00:04:41,615
Who is it?

29
00:04:59,299 --> 00:05:01,051
Okay. You got me.
Very funny.

30
00:05:04,679 --> 00:05:07,974
Right, I've got the joke!
Whose idea was this?

31
00:05:09,059 --> 00:05:10,977
Is it Derek's?
Is it?

32
00:05:13,188 --> 00:05:14,481
Derek, is this you?

33
00:05:36,044 --> 00:05:37,212
(WHIMPERS)

34
00:05:38,672 --> 00:05:39,714
Run!

35
00:06:03,613 --> 00:06:05,073
(GRUNTING)

36
00:06:09,911 --> 00:06:13,582
-You pulled his arm off!
-Yep, plastic.

37
00:06:13,748 --> 00:06:16,459
Very clever, nice trick.
Who are they then, students?

38
00:06:16,585 --> 00:06:17,878
Is this a student thing
or what?

39
00:06:17,961 --> 00:06:20,380
-Why would they be students?
-I don't know!

40
00:06:20,630 --> 00:06:22,132
Well, you said it.
Why students?

41
00:06:22,465 --> 00:06:25,719
'Cause... To get that many
people dressed up and being silly,

42
00:06:25,802 --> 00:06:26,928
they got to be students.

43
00:06:27,762 --> 00:06:28,805
That makes sense. Well done.

44
00:06:29,472 --> 00:06:30,724
-Thanks.
-They're not students.

45
00:06:30,807 --> 00:06:33,310
Whoever they are, when Wilson finds
them, he's going to call the police.

46
00:06:33,393 --> 00:06:35,103
-Who's Wilson?
-Chief electrician.

47
00:06:35,312 --> 00:06:36,396
Wilson's dead.

48
00:06:38,773 --> 00:06:40,317
-That's just not funny. That's sick!
-Hold on!

49
00:06:40,400 --> 00:06:42,819
-Mind your eyes.
-I've had enough of this now.

50
00:06:43,320 --> 00:06:46,990
(WHIMPERS) Who are you, then?
Who's that lot down there?

51
00:06:47,490 --> 00:06:49,159
I said who are they?

52
00:06:49,492 --> 00:06:52,495
They're made of plastic.
Living plastic creatures.

53
00:06:52,871 --> 00:06:55,081
And they're being controlled
by a relay device on the roof.

54
00:06:55,165 --> 00:06:58,126
Which would be a great big
problem if I didn't have this.

55
00:06:58,209 --> 00:07:01,004
So, I'm gonna go upstairs
and blow it up.

56
00:07:01,129 --> 00:07:03,089
And I might well die in the
process, but don't worry about me.

57
00:07:03,173 --> 00:07:06,718
No, you go home. Go on, go and have
your lovely beans on toast.

58
00:07:06,843 --> 00:07:10,180
Don't tell anyone about this, 'cause
if you do, you'll get them killed.

59
00:07:13,516 --> 00:07:14,476
I'm the Doctor, by the way.

60
00:07:14,559 --> 00:07:15,685
-What's your name?
-Rose.

61
00:07:15,852 --> 00:07:17,812
Nice to meet you, Rose.
Run for your life!

62
00:07:49,177 --> 00:07:50,679
-(CAR HONKING)
-(GASPS)

63
00:07:50,762 --> 00:07:52,597
(DRIVER SHOUTS INDISTINCTLY)

64
00:07:57,268 --> 00:07:58,353
(LOUD EXPLOSION)

65
00:08:12,784 --> 00:08:14,995
REPORTER: The whole of Central
London has been closed off

66
00:08:15,412 --> 00:08:16,871
as police investigate
the fire.

67
00:08:18,873 --> 00:08:23,420
I know, it's on the telly! It's
everywhere, she's lucky to be alive.

68
00:08:23,712 --> 00:08:26,589
Honestly, it's aged her.
Skin like an old Bible.

69
00:08:26,715 --> 00:08:28,883
He's walking in now.
You'd think I was her daughter.

70
00:08:28,967 --> 00:08:30,301
Oh, and here's himself.

71
00:08:31,052 --> 00:08:32,929
I've been phoning your mobile!
You could have been dead!

72
00:08:33,054 --> 00:08:34,264
It's on the news
and everything!

73
00:08:34,389 --> 00:08:36,224
I can't believe
that your shop went up!

74
00:08:36,307 --> 00:08:38,977
I'm all right.
Honestly, I'm fine. Don't make a fuss!

75
00:08:39,102 --> 00:08:41,104
-But what happened?
-I don't know.

76
00:08:41,479 --> 00:08:42,772
What was it though?
What caused it?

77
00:08:42,897 --> 00:08:45,150
I wasn't in the shop.
I was outside. Didn't see anything.

78
00:08:45,275 --> 00:08:49,112
It's Debbie. She knows a man on
The Mirror, 500 quid for an interview.

79
00:08:49,237 --> 00:08:51,114
Oh, that's brilliant,
give it here.

80
00:08:51,823 --> 00:08:52,907
(PHONE BEEPS)

81
00:08:53,950 --> 00:08:55,827
You've got to find some way
of making money.

82
00:08:55,952 --> 00:08:58,371
Your job's kaput
and I'm not bailing you out.

83
00:08:58,455 --> 00:08:59,581
(PHONE RINGS)

84
00:09:00,623 --> 00:09:02,167
Bey, she's alive!

85
00:09:02,625 --> 00:09:05,211
I've told her,
sue for compensation.

86
00:09:05,295 --> 00:09:07,130
She was within
seconds of death!

87
00:09:07,422 --> 00:09:09,883
What are you drinking, tea? No, no, no.
That's no good! That's no good!

88
00:09:09,966 --> 00:09:11,009
You're in shock.

89
00:09:11,092 --> 00:09:12,260
-You need something stronger.
-I'm all right.

90
00:09:12,427 --> 00:09:14,512
Now, come one. You deserve a proper
drink. We're going down the pub.

91
00:09:14,637 --> 00:09:16,014
You and me, my treat.
How about it?

92
00:09:16,139 --> 00:09:18,433
Is there a match on?

93
00:09:18,516 --> 00:09:20,393
No, no.
I'm just thinking about you!

94
00:09:20,477 --> 00:09:21,853
There's a match on,
ain't there?

95
00:09:22,479 --> 00:09:24,898
Well that's not the point. But we
could catch the last five minutes.

96
00:09:24,981 --> 00:09:27,192
Go on, then.
I'm fine, really, go.

97
00:09:27,484 --> 00:09:28,526
And get rid of that.

98
00:09:33,490 --> 00:09:34,657
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

99
00:09:38,661 --> 00:09:40,163
-Bye-bye.
-Bye!

100
00:09:40,288 --> 00:09:41,539
(IMITATES CHOKING)

101
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:46,669
Fifteen fire crews are
in attendance,

102
00:09:46,795 --> 00:09:49,506
though it's thought there's very little
chance of saving the infrastructure.

103
00:09:51,132 --> 00:09:53,009
(MAN AND WOMAN ARGUING)

104
00:10:08,024 --> 00:10:10,485
(ALARM CLOCK BUZZES)

105
00:10:19,244 --> 00:10:23,498
There's no point in getting up,
sweetheart. You've no job to go to.

106
00:10:28,211 --> 00:10:31,881
There's Finch's.
You could try them.

107
00:10:32,549 --> 00:10:34,592
-They've always got jobs.
-Oh, great, the butcher's.

108
00:10:34,717 --> 00:10:37,720
It might do you good. That shop
was giving you airs and graces.

109
00:10:38,012 --> 00:10:40,306
I'm not joking about
compensation.

110
00:10:40,390 --> 00:10:42,100
You've had genuine
shock and trauma.

111
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:44,602
Ariana got two thousand
quid off the council

112
00:10:44,727 --> 00:10:47,397
just because the old man behind
the desk said she looked Greek!

113
00:10:48,356 --> 00:10:50,233
I know she is Greek,
but that's not the point.

114
00:10:50,733 --> 00:10:52,235
It was a valid claim.

115
00:10:54,612 --> 00:10:55,655
(RATTLING)

116
00:10:55,738 --> 00:10:56,823
(PATTERING)

117
00:10:56,906 --> 00:10:59,993
Mum, you're such a liar!
I said to nail that cat-flap down.

118
00:11:00,076 --> 00:11:01,327
We're gonna get strays!

119
00:11:01,411 --> 00:11:04,247
-I did it weeks back.
-Nah, you thought about it.

120
00:11:05,957 --> 00:11:07,041
(RATTLES)

121
00:11:19,262 --> 00:11:20,305
(GASPS)

122
00:11:21,598 --> 00:11:23,308
-What are you doing here?
-I live here.

123
00:11:23,600 --> 00:11:25,768
-What do you do that for?
-'Cause I do!

124
00:11:26,060 --> 00:11:28,229
I'm only home
"cause someone blew up my job!

125
00:11:28,605 --> 00:11:29,981
Must have got
the wrong signal.

126
00:11:30,106 --> 00:11:32,692
You're not plastic,
are you? Nope, bonehead. Bye, then!

127
00:11:32,775 --> 00:11:35,069
You, inside, right now.

128
00:11:35,403 --> 00:11:36,446
Who is it?

129
00:11:38,448 --> 00:11:41,784
It's about last night. He's part
of the inquiry. Give us 10 minutes.

130
00:11:41,910 --> 00:11:44,287
She deserves compensation!

131
00:11:44,412 --> 00:11:45,622
Oh, we're talking millions.

132
00:11:46,956 --> 00:11:49,667
I'm... (CLEARS THROAT)
I'm in my dressing gown.

133
00:11:50,668 --> 00:11:51,753
Yes, you are.

134
00:11:53,421 --> 00:11:54,923
There's a strange man
in my bedroom.

135
00:11:56,257 --> 00:11:57,300
Yes, there is.

136
00:11:59,427 --> 00:12:01,095
Well, anything could happen.

137
00:12:03,014 --> 00:12:04,098
No.

138
00:12:07,810 --> 00:12:10,104
Don't mind the mess.
Do you want a coffee?

139
00:12:10,188 --> 00:12:11,481
Might as well, thanks,
just milk.

140
00:12:12,649 --> 00:12:14,150
We should go
to the police.

141
00:12:14,525 --> 00:12:15,693
Seriously.
Both of us.

142
00:12:15,818 --> 00:12:17,779
That won't last.
He's gay and she's an alien.

143
00:12:17,862 --> 00:12:20,990
I'm not blaming you, even if
it was some sort of joke...

144
00:12:21,115 --> 00:12:22,158
Mmm. Sad ending.

145
00:12:23,618 --> 00:12:26,496
-It said on the news they found a body.
-"Rose Tyler."

146
00:12:28,289 --> 00:12:31,042
Ah, could've been worse.
Look at the ears!

147
00:12:31,167 --> 00:12:33,711
...all the same, he was nice.
He was a nice bloke.

148
00:12:35,004 --> 00:12:37,048
Anyway, if we are gonna
go to the police,

149
00:12:37,382 --> 00:12:38,508
I wanna know
what I'm saying.

150
00:12:39,175 --> 00:12:41,636
-I want you to explain everything.
-Maybe not.

151
00:12:41,719 --> 00:12:43,179
-(PATTERING)
-What's that then?

152
00:12:44,889 --> 00:12:46,015
Have you got a cat?

153
00:12:46,391 --> 00:12:47,809
No.

154
00:12:48,893 --> 00:12:52,855
We did have, but we just get
strays. They come in off the estate.

155
00:12:57,068 --> 00:12:58,444
(DOCTOR GRUNTING)

156
00:12:58,528 --> 00:13:00,488
I told Mickey
to chuck that out.

157
00:13:01,322 --> 00:13:03,533
You're all the same.
Give a man a plastic hand...

158
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:07,203
Anyway, I don't even
know your name. Doctor what was it?

159
00:13:09,539 --> 00:13:10,581
(SHRIEKS)

160
00:13:16,671 --> 00:13:17,714
(HAIR BLOWER WHIRRING)

161
00:13:29,392 --> 00:13:30,435
(BEEPING)

162
00:13:35,064 --> 00:13:36,607
(HIGH-PITCHED BEEPING)

163
00:13:36,733 --> 00:13:37,984
It's all right,
I've stopped it.

164
00:13:38,067 --> 00:13:41,404
-There you go, you see, arm less!
-Do you think?

165
00:13:41,571 --> 00:13:42,572
Ow!

166
00:13:44,198 --> 00:13:46,576
ROSE: Hold on a minute,
you can't just go swanning off!

167
00:13:46,701 --> 00:13:49,370
Yes. I can. Here I am.
This is me, swanning off, see ya!

168
00:13:49,454 --> 00:13:51,873
ROSE: That arm was moving,
it tried to kill me!

169
00:13:51,956 --> 00:13:53,374
DOCTOR: Ten out of ten
for observation.

170
00:13:53,458 --> 00:13:55,585
You can't just walk away.
That's not fair.

171
00:13:55,710 --> 00:13:57,211
You've got to tell me
what's going on.

172
00:13:57,295 --> 00:13:58,379
No, I don't.

173
00:14:01,632 --> 00:14:04,552
All right, then. I'll go
to the police. I'll tell everyone.

174
00:14:05,303 --> 00:14:09,599
You said if I did that
I'd get people killed, so, your choice.

175
00:14:09,891 --> 00:14:11,851
Tell me or I'll start talking.

176
00:14:11,934 --> 00:14:14,771
-Is that supposed to sound tough?
-Sort of.

177
00:14:14,896 --> 00:14:15,980
Doesn't work.

178
00:14:16,773 --> 00:14:19,275
-Who are you?
-Told you, the Doctor.

179
00:14:19,650 --> 00:14:20,985
Yeah, but Doctor what?

180
00:14:21,110 --> 00:14:23,154
-Just the Doctor.
-The Doctor?

181
00:14:23,279 --> 00:14:24,447
Hello!

182
00:14:25,615 --> 00:14:27,617
Is that supposed
to sound impressive?

183
00:14:27,950 --> 00:14:28,993
Sort of.

184
00:14:29,619 --> 00:14:33,331
Come on then,
you can tell me. I've seen enough.

185
00:14:34,582 --> 00:14:38,252
-Are you the police?
-No! I was just passing through.

186
00:14:38,795 --> 00:14:39,962
I'm a long way from home...

187
00:14:40,088 --> 00:14:43,841
What have I done wrong? How come those
plastic things keep coming after me?

188
00:14:43,966 --> 00:14:46,469
Oh, suddenly
the entire world revolves around you.

189
00:14:46,594 --> 00:14:48,846
You were just an accident.
You got in the way, that's all.

190
00:14:48,971 --> 00:14:51,516
-It tried to kill me!
-It was after me, not you!

191
00:14:51,641 --> 00:14:54,018
Last night, in the shop,
I was there, you blundered in,

192
00:14:54,143 --> 00:14:55,436
almost ruined the whole thing.

193
00:14:55,520 --> 00:14:58,689
This morning, I was tracking it
down, it was tracking me down...

194
00:14:59,148 --> 00:15:01,317
The only reason it fixed
on you is because you met me.

195
00:15:01,442 --> 00:15:05,655
So, what you're saying
is the entire world revolves around you?

196
00:15:05,780 --> 00:15:07,907
-Sort of, yeah.
-You're full of it!

197
00:15:07,990 --> 00:15:09,617
Sort of, yeah.

198
00:15:11,119 --> 00:15:13,579
All this plastic stuff,
who else knows about it?

199
00:15:13,663 --> 00:15:15,039
No one.

200
00:15:15,164 --> 00:15:16,666
What, you're on your own?

201
00:15:17,667 --> 00:15:20,294
Well, who else is there? I mean,
you lot, all you do is eat chips,

202
00:15:20,378 --> 00:15:21,587
got to bed and watch telly,

203
00:15:21,671 --> 00:15:24,715
while all the time
underneath you, there's a war going on.

204
00:15:26,175 --> 00:15:28,719
Okay. Start from
the beginning.

205
00:15:30,847 --> 00:15:34,434
I mean, if we're going with the living
plastic, and I don't even believe that,

206
00:15:34,517 --> 00:15:36,644
but if we do...
How did you kill it?

207
00:15:37,353 --> 00:15:41,315
The thing controlling it projects life
into the arm. Cut off the signal - dead.

208
00:15:41,399 --> 00:15:43,860
-So, that's radio control?
-Thought control.

209
00:15:45,736 --> 00:15:47,572
-You all right?
-Yeah.

210
00:15:48,072 --> 00:15:49,615
So who's
controlling it, then?

211
00:15:49,699 --> 00:15:51,742
-Long story.
-What's it all for?

212
00:15:51,868 --> 00:15:55,079
I mean, shop window dummies,
what's that about?

213
00:15:55,997 --> 00:15:57,665
Is someone trying
to take over Britain's shops?

214
00:15:57,748 --> 00:15:59,041
(BOTH CHUCKLING)

215
00:15:59,167 --> 00:16:00,334
No!

216
00:16:00,751 --> 00:16:03,087
-Well, no!
-It's not a price war.

217
00:16:03,212 --> 00:16:04,755
(BOTH LAUGHING)

218
00:16:06,174 --> 00:16:08,509
They want to overthrow
the human race and destroy you.

219
00:16:09,886 --> 00:16:11,596
-Do you believe me?
-No.

220
00:16:11,721 --> 00:16:13,055
But you're still listening.

221
00:16:14,682 --> 00:16:17,894
Really, though, Doctor,
tell me, who are you?

222
00:16:23,774 --> 00:16:26,694
Do you know like we were saying?
About the Earth revolving?

223
00:16:29,864 --> 00:16:31,782
It's like when you're a kid.

224
00:16:31,908 --> 00:16:33,993
The first time they tell you
that the world's turning

225
00:16:34,076 --> 00:16:35,453
and you just can't quite believe it

226
00:16:35,578 --> 00:16:37,455
'cause everything looks
like it's standing still.

227
00:16:41,083 --> 00:16:42,418
I can feel it.

228
00:16:45,087 --> 00:16:47,048
The turn of the Earth.

229
00:16:47,882 --> 00:16:50,968
The ground beneath our feet
is spinning at 1,000 miles an hour.

230
00:16:51,469 --> 00:16:55,598
And the entire planet is hurtling
round the sun at 67,000 miles an hour.

231
00:16:55,932 --> 00:16:58,976
I can feel it,
we're falling through space, you and me.

232
00:17:00,102 --> 00:17:03,439
Clinging to the skin of this
tiny little world, and if we let go...

233
00:17:07,443 --> 00:17:08,861
That's who I am.

234
00:17:08,945 --> 00:17:10,821
Now forget me, Rose Tyler.

235
00:17:12,740 --> 00:17:13,783
Go home.

236
00:17:43,020 --> 00:17:44,939
(WIND BLOWING)

237
00:17:46,482 --> 00:17:48,359
(TARDIS WHOOSHING)

238
00:18:17,680 --> 00:18:20,683
-Hey, here's my woman! Kit off.
-Oh, shut up.

239
00:18:22,727 --> 00:18:25,479
-Coffee?
-Yeah, only if you wash the mug.

240
00:18:25,563 --> 00:18:27,982
And I don't mean rinse,
I mean wash. Can I use your computer?

241
00:18:28,065 --> 00:18:30,484
Yeah, any excuse
to get in the bedroom.

242
00:18:32,320 --> 00:18:34,030
Don't read my e-mails!

243
00:19:18,074 --> 00:19:19,116
ROSE: You're not
coming in.

244
00:19:20,409 --> 00:19:22,703
He's safe, he's got
a wife and kids.

245
00:19:22,787 --> 00:19:23,871
Yeah, who told you that?

246
00:19:23,954 --> 00:19:27,958
He did. That's exactly what an
internet lunatic murderer would say.

247
00:19:32,129 --> 00:19:33,214
(KNOCKING)

248
00:19:35,633 --> 00:19:36,717
(SIGHS)

249
00:19:46,727 --> 00:19:47,770
(KNOCKING)

250
00:19:52,108 --> 00:19:55,945
Um, hello, I've come
to see Clive. We've been e-mailing.

251
00:19:56,153 --> 00:19:59,156
Oh, Dad! It's one
of your nutters.

252
00:20:02,660 --> 00:20:06,497
Sorry, hello!
You must be Rose. I'm Clive. Obviously.

253
00:20:06,789 --> 00:20:09,458
I'd better tell you now,
my boyfriend's in the car,

254
00:20:09,583 --> 00:20:11,168
just in case you're gonna
kill me!

255
00:20:11,293 --> 00:20:13,003
(LAUGHS) No, good point!
No murders!

256
00:20:14,296 --> 00:20:15,297
WOMAN: Who is it?

257
00:20:15,423 --> 00:20:17,341
Oh, it's something to do
with the Doctor.

258
00:20:17,466 --> 00:20:18,676
She's been reading
the website.

259
00:20:18,801 --> 00:20:20,302
Please come through.
I'm in the shed.

260
00:20:22,304 --> 00:20:27,476
She? She's read a website
about the Doctor, she's a she?

261
00:20:32,314 --> 00:20:33,733
CLIVE: A lot of this stuff is
quite sensitive,

262
00:20:33,816 --> 00:20:35,276
I couldn't just send it to you.

263
00:20:35,359 --> 00:20:36,986
People might intercept...

264
00:20:37,111 --> 00:20:38,320
If you know what I mean.

265
00:20:38,821 --> 00:20:39,947
If you dig deep enough

266
00:20:40,489 --> 00:20:42,116
and keep a lively mind,

267
00:20:42,199 --> 00:20:44,618
this Doctor keeps
cropping up all over the place.

268
00:20:44,994 --> 00:20:48,664
Political diaries,
conspiracy theories, even ghost stories.

269
00:20:49,665 --> 00:20:52,835
No first name, no last name,
just "the Doctor”.

270
00:20:53,669 --> 00:20:54,837
Always the Doctor.

271
00:20:55,796 --> 00:20:58,382
And the title seems to be
passed down from father to son,

272
00:20:58,507 --> 00:21:00,009
appears to be
an inheritance.

273
00:21:00,134 --> 00:21:01,969
That's your Doctor
there, isn't it?

274
00:21:02,470 --> 00:21:03,471
Yeah.

275
00:21:03,554 --> 00:21:06,891
I tracked it down to the Washington
Public Archive, just last year.

276
00:21:07,016 --> 00:21:10,853
The online photo's enhanced,
but if we look at the original...

277
00:21:23,532 --> 00:21:27,912
November 22nd 1963,
the assassination of President Kennedy.

278
00:21:28,496 --> 00:21:29,538
See?

279
00:21:31,415 --> 00:21:33,000
Must be his father.

280
00:21:33,209 --> 00:21:34,585
Going further back,

281
00:21:35,169 --> 00:21:36,712
April 1912,

282
00:21:38,672 --> 00:21:41,383
this is a photograph of
the Daniels family of Southampton

283
00:21:41,884 --> 00:21:42,927
and friend.

284
00:21:43,761 --> 00:21:47,348
Taken the day before they were due to
sail to the new world. On the Titanic.

285
00:21:48,098 --> 00:21:51,227
And for some unknown reason,
they cancelled the trip, and survived.

286
00:21:51,936 --> 00:21:53,729
And here we are,

287
00:21:55,272 --> 00:21:57,525
1883, another Doctor.

288
00:21:58,025 --> 00:22:00,611
Look, the same lineage,
he's identical.

289
00:22:01,904 --> 00:22:03,739
This one washed up
on the coast of Sumatra,

290
00:22:03,864 --> 00:22:06,075
and the very night
the Krakatoa exploded.

291
00:22:07,243 --> 00:22:09,912
The Doctor is a legend
woven throughout history.

292
00:22:10,454 --> 00:22:12,248
When disaster comes,
he's there.

293
00:22:13,082 --> 00:22:14,458
He brings the storm
in his wake.

294
00:22:15,251 --> 00:22:17,753
-And he has one constant companion.
-Who's that?

295
00:22:19,088 --> 00:22:20,130
Death.

296
00:22:43,487 --> 00:22:46,407
If the Doctor's back,
if you've seen him, Rose,

297
00:22:47,283 --> 00:22:48,909
then one thing's for certain.

298
00:22:50,119 --> 00:22:51,579
We're all in danger.

299
00:23:27,323 --> 00:23:28,365
Come on then.

300
00:23:28,991 --> 00:23:32,119
If he singled you out,
if the Doctor's making house calls,

301
00:23:35,873 --> 00:23:37,458
then God help you.

302
00:23:50,512 --> 00:23:51,847
(BIN GROWLS)

303
00:24:07,696 --> 00:24:09,490
(GRUNTING)

304
00:24:15,537 --> 00:24:16,664
(SCREAMS)

305
00:24:19,708 --> 00:24:20,751
(BIN BELCHES)

306
00:24:21,251 --> 00:24:22,544
But who is he?

307
00:24:22,878 --> 00:24:24,004
Who do you think he is?

308
00:24:24,880 --> 00:24:26,215
I think he's the same man.

309
00:24:27,675 --> 00:24:28,842
I think he's immortal.

310
00:24:31,387 --> 00:24:33,764
I think he's an alien
from another world.

311
00:24:36,892 --> 00:24:38,978
All right, he's a nutter.
Off his head.

312
00:24:39,061 --> 00:24:42,690
Complete online
conspiracy freak, you win!

313
00:24:43,607 --> 00:24:45,901
(SIGHS) What are we
going to do tonight?

314
00:24:46,568 --> 00:24:47,695
I fancy a pizza.

315
00:24:47,778 --> 00:24:50,239
Pizza! (STAMMERING)

316
00:24:50,739 --> 00:24:52,449
-Pizza!
-Or Chinese.

317
00:24:52,908 --> 00:24:54,410
Pizza!

318
00:25:05,921 --> 00:25:07,673
Do you think I should
try the hospital?

319
00:25:07,756 --> 00:25:10,175
Suki said they had jobs going
in the canteen.

320
00:25:11,510 --> 00:25:14,388
Is that it then,
dishing out chips?

321
00:25:15,389 --> 00:25:17,433
I could do A-levels.
I don't know.

322
00:25:18,559 --> 00:25:20,936
It's all Jimmy Stone's fault.

323
00:25:21,020 --> 00:25:22,938
I went and left school
because of him, look where I ended up.

324
00:25:24,064 --> 00:25:25,190
What do you think?

325
00:25:26,025 --> 00:25:27,276
So where did you
meet this Doctor?

326
00:25:27,359 --> 00:25:29,862
I'm sorry,
was I talking about me for a second?

327
00:25:29,945 --> 00:25:32,197
'Cause I reckon it all
started back at the shop, am I right?

328
00:25:32,281 --> 00:25:34,450
-Was he something to do with that?
-No.

329
00:25:34,700 --> 00:25:35,743
Come on.

330
00:25:37,244 --> 00:25:38,287
Sort of.

331
00:25:39,788 --> 00:25:40,831
What was he doing there?

332
00:25:40,914 --> 00:25:43,584
I'm not going on about it,
Mickey, really I'm not.

333
00:25:44,376 --> 00:25:46,128
'Cause I know it
sounds daft, but,

334
00:25:46,879 --> 00:25:48,255
I don't think he's safe.

335
00:25:48,756 --> 00:25:51,633
-He's dangerous.
-But you can trust me, sweetheart.

336
00:25:51,717 --> 00:25:54,136
(MALFUNCTIONING ROBOTIC VOICE)
Babe, darling, sugar...

337
00:25:54,970 --> 00:25:58,390
You can tell me anything. Tell me about
the Doctor and what he's planning,

338
00:25:58,474 --> 00:26:00,225
and I can help you, Rose.

339
00:26:00,309 --> 00:26:02,061
That's all I want to do,
sweetheart.

340
00:26:02,144 --> 00:26:04,396
Darling, babe, babe,
sugar, sweetheart.

341
00:26:04,480 --> 00:26:06,148
What are you doing that for?

342
00:26:06,440 --> 00:26:08,817
-Your champagne.
-We didn't order any champagne.

343
00:26:08,942 --> 00:26:11,487
-Where's the Doctor?
-Madam, your champagne.

344
00:26:12,654 --> 00:26:15,491
It's not ours.
Mickey, what is it, what's wrong?

345
00:26:15,783 --> 00:26:17,993
I need to find out
how much he knows, so where is he?

346
00:26:18,285 --> 00:26:21,455
-Doesn't anybody want this champagne?
-Look, we didn't order...

347
00:26:22,664 --> 00:26:25,000
-Ah, got you.
-Don't mind me.

348
00:26:25,459 --> 00:26:27,002
I'm just toasting
the happy couple.

349
00:26:27,628 --> 00:26:28,670
On the house!

350
00:26:36,637 --> 00:26:37,679
Anyway!

351
00:26:38,514 --> 00:26:40,140
(WOMAN SCREAMS)

352
00:26:49,858 --> 00:26:51,360
Don't think that's
gonna stop me.

353
00:26:51,443 --> 00:26:52,861
(SCREAMS)

354
00:26:55,030 --> 00:26:57,032
-(ALARM RINGS)
-Everyone, out! Out now!

355
00:27:01,620 --> 00:27:04,039
Get out, get out, get out!

356
00:27:25,853 --> 00:27:28,564
Open the gate!
Use that tube thing! Come on!

357
00:27:28,897 --> 00:27:30,858
-Sonic screwdriver.
-Use it!

358
00:27:31,191 --> 00:27:33,026
Nah, tell you what,
let's go in here.

359
00:27:39,533 --> 00:27:41,410
You can't hide
inside a wooden box!

360
00:27:46,582 --> 00:27:48,083
He's gonna get us!

361
00:27:50,169 --> 00:27:51,211
Doctor!

362
00:28:18,238 --> 00:28:19,448
It's gonna follow us.

363
00:28:19,531 --> 00:28:22,284
The assembled hordes of Genghis Khan
couldn't get through that door.

364
00:28:22,367 --> 00:28:24,953
Believe me, they've tried!
Now, shut up a minute.

365
00:28:34,713 --> 00:28:39,468
You see, the arm
was too simple, but the head's perfect.

366
00:28:39,885 --> 00:28:43,305
I can use it to trace
the signal back to the original source.

367
00:28:45,224 --> 00:28:47,309
Right. Where do you
want to start?

368
00:28:47,434 --> 00:28:50,896
Um... The inside's bigger
than the outside.

369
00:28:51,146 --> 00:28:53,232
-Yes.
-It's alien.

370
00:28:53,607 --> 00:28:54,650
Yep.

371
00:28:55,984 --> 00:28:57,069
Are you alien?

372
00:28:57,986 --> 00:28:59,071
Yes.

373
00:29:00,822 --> 00:29:02,241
-Is that all right?
-Yeah.

374
00:29:02,950 --> 00:29:04,243
It's called the Tardis,
this thing.

375
00:29:04,326 --> 00:29:08,580
T-A-R-D-I-S, that's Time And
Relative Dimension In Space.

376
00:29:09,456 --> 00:29:10,582
(SOBBING)

377
00:29:10,666 --> 00:29:12,668
That's okay. Culture shock.

378
00:29:12,793 --> 00:29:15,504
-Happens to the best of us.
-Did they kill him? Mickey?

379
00:29:16,296 --> 00:29:18,173
Did they kill Mickey?
Is he dead?

380
00:29:18,840 --> 00:29:20,801
Oh, I didn't think of that.

381
00:29:21,301 --> 00:29:24,471
He's my boyfriend.
You pulled off his head.

382
00:29:24,846 --> 00:29:27,015
They copied him,
and you didn't even think.

383
00:29:27,099 --> 00:29:29,184
-And now you're just gonna let him melt.
-Melt?

384
00:29:32,312 --> 00:29:34,481
Aw, no, no, no, no!

385
00:29:35,440 --> 00:29:38,193
-What are you doing?
-Following the signal. It's fading!

386
00:29:39,987 --> 00:29:41,280
Wait a minute.
I've got it.

387
00:29:42,114 --> 00:29:44,032
No, no, no, no, no, no, no!

388
00:29:46,493 --> 00:29:48,787
Almost there, almost there.

389
00:29:48,870 --> 00:29:50,289
Here we go!

390
00:29:50,372 --> 00:29:52,291
(RUMBLING)

391
00:29:54,209 --> 00:29:56,044
You can't go out there.
It's not safe!

392
00:30:01,049 --> 00:30:03,218
I lost the signal.
I got so close.

393
00:30:03,552 --> 00:30:04,678
(DOOR SLAMS)

394
00:30:05,721 --> 00:30:07,556
We've moved.
Does it fly?

395
00:30:08,015 --> 00:30:10,809
It disappears there and reappears
here. You wouldn't understand.

396
00:30:10,892 --> 00:30:14,396
But if we're somewhere else, what about
that headless thing that's on the loose?

397
00:30:14,730 --> 00:30:17,190
Melted with the head.
Are you going to witter on all night?

398
00:30:18,025 --> 00:30:19,901
I'LL have to tell his mother.

399
00:30:22,988 --> 00:30:25,741
Mickey... I'll have to
tell his mother he's dead,

400
00:30:25,824 --> 00:30:27,868
and you just went and
forgot him, again!

401
00:30:28,744 --> 00:30:29,995
You were right.
You are alien.

402
00:30:30,370 --> 00:30:33,165
-If I forgot some kid called Mickey...
-He's not a kid!

403
00:30:33,248 --> 00:30:36,001
...it's because I'm trying
to save the life of every stupid ape

404
00:30:36,084 --> 00:30:38,253
blundering about
on this planet, all right?

405
00:30:38,378 --> 00:30:40,047
-All right?
-Yes, it is!

406
00:30:42,257 --> 00:30:44,593
If you are an alien, why do you
sound like you're from the north?

407
00:30:44,676 --> 00:30:46,386
Lots of planets have a north!

408
00:30:48,263 --> 00:30:51,600
(STAMMERS) What's a police
public call box?

409
00:30:53,769 --> 00:30:57,606
It's a telephone box,
from the 1950s. It's a disguise.

410
00:30:58,774 --> 00:31:03,278
(CHUCKLES) Okay... And, this living
plastic, what's it got against us?

411
00:31:03,612 --> 00:31:07,115
Nothing. It loves you. You've got such
a good planet, lots of smoke and oil,

412
00:31:07,199 --> 00:31:10,243
plenty of toxins and dioxins
in the air. Perfect.

413
00:31:10,786 --> 00:31:12,954
Just what the Nestene
Consciousness needs.

414
00:31:13,080 --> 00:31:16,625
Its food stock was destroyed in the
war, its protein planets rotted.

415
00:31:16,708 --> 00:31:19,211
-So. Earth. Dinner.
-Any way of stopping it?

416
00:31:20,128 --> 00:31:21,296
Antiplastic.

417
00:31:21,713 --> 00:31:23,423
-Antiplastic?
-Antiplastic!

418
00:31:24,424 --> 00:31:25,634
But first,
I've got to find it.

419
00:31:25,717 --> 00:31:28,053
How can you hide
something that big in a city this small?

420
00:31:28,136 --> 00:31:30,222
-Hold on, hide what?
-The transmitter.

421
00:31:30,972 --> 00:31:33,725
The Consciousness is controlling
every single piece of plastic,

422
00:31:33,975 --> 00:31:35,811
so it needs a transmitter
to boost the signal.

423
00:31:35,894 --> 00:31:37,729
-What does it look like?
-Like a transmitter!

424
00:31:37,813 --> 00:31:41,149
Round and massive, somewhere
slap-bang in the middle of London.

425
00:31:41,733 --> 00:31:46,238
A huge, metal, circular structure
like a dish, like a wheel, radial,

426
00:31:46,321 --> 00:31:47,406
close to where we're standing.

427
00:31:47,489 --> 00:31:48,782
It must be
completely invisible.

428
00:31:49,991 --> 00:31:51,076
What?

429
00:31:53,745 --> 00:31:54,788
What?

430
00:31:57,499 --> 00:31:58,542
What is it? What?

431
00:32:02,838 --> 00:32:03,922
Oh.

432
00:32:06,049 --> 00:32:07,134
Fantastic!

433
00:32:29,448 --> 00:32:31,575
Think of it.
Plastic all over the world,

434
00:32:31,658 --> 00:32:33,827
every artificial thing
waiting to be alive.

435
00:32:34,286 --> 00:32:37,164
The shop window dummies,
the phones, the wires, the cables.

436
00:32:37,247 --> 00:32:38,582
The breast implants.

437
00:32:38,665 --> 00:32:40,333
Still, we've found
the transmitter.

438
00:32:40,417 --> 00:32:42,878
The Consciousness must be
somewhere underneath.

439
00:32:46,006 --> 00:32:47,674
What about down here?

440
00:32:51,553 --> 00:32:52,929
Looks good to me.

441
00:33:37,307 --> 00:33:39,059
The Nestene Consciousness.

442
00:33:39,142 --> 00:33:42,562
That's it, inside the vat,
a living plastic creature.

443
00:33:42,646 --> 00:33:44,814
Well then, tip in
your Antiplastic and let's go.

444
00:33:45,315 --> 00:33:48,360
I'm not here to kill it.
I've got to give it a chance.

445
00:33:56,117 --> 00:34:00,121
I seek audience with the Nestene
Consciousness under peaceful contract

446
00:34:00,205 --> 00:34:03,667
according to Convention 15
of the Shadow Proclamation.

447
00:34:04,125 --> 00:34:05,835
(GURGLES)

448
00:34:06,461 --> 00:34:08,547
Thank you. If I might have
permission to approach.

449
00:34:12,259 --> 00:34:13,301
Oh, my God.

450
00:34:16,221 --> 00:34:18,974
Mickey! It's me!
It's okay.

451
00:34:19,057 --> 00:34:21,184
-It's all right. It's all right.
-Shhh.

452
00:34:21,268 --> 00:34:24,229
That thing, down there...
The liquid, Rose, it can talk!

453
00:34:24,396 --> 00:34:25,689
Oh, you're stinking!

454
00:34:26,273 --> 00:34:27,524
Doctor, they kept him alive!

455
00:34:27,607 --> 00:34:31,528
Yeah, that was always a possibility,
keep him alive to maintain the copy.

456
00:34:31,611 --> 00:34:33,655
You knew that and never said?

457
00:34:33,822 --> 00:34:34,864
Can we keep the domestics
outside, thank you?

458
00:34:42,247 --> 00:34:43,957
(NESTENE GURGLING)

459
00:34:48,878 --> 00:34:50,463
Am I addressing
the Consciousness?

460
00:34:52,674 --> 00:34:54,593
Thank you.
If I might observe,

461
00:34:54,676 --> 00:34:59,139
you infiltrated this civilization by
means of warped, shunt technology.

462
00:34:59,222 --> 00:35:02,517
So, may I suggest, with the greatest
respect, that you shunt off?

463
00:35:03,059 --> 00:35:04,603
(GROWLING)

464
00:35:04,686 --> 00:35:07,939
Oh, don't give me that!
It's an invasion, plain and simple.

465
00:35:08,023 --> 00:35:10,400
Don't talk about
constitutional rights.

466
00:35:12,485 --> 00:35:14,154
I am talking!

467
00:35:17,282 --> 00:35:18,658
This planet is just starting.

468
00:35:18,742 --> 00:35:22,287
These stupid little people
have only just learned how to walk.

469
00:35:22,370 --> 00:35:24,456
But they're capable
of so much more.

470
00:35:24,539 --> 00:35:28,001
I'm asking you,
on their behalf. Please, just go.

471
00:35:28,168 --> 00:35:29,210
Doctor!

472
00:35:35,008 --> 00:35:37,510
That was just insurance!
I wasn't gonna use it.

473
00:35:38,803 --> 00:35:40,138
(GROWLING)

474
00:35:40,597 --> 00:35:42,891
I was not attacking you.
I'm here to help.

475
00:35:42,974 --> 00:35:45,185
I'm not your enemy,
I swear, I'm not.

476
00:35:48,063 --> 00:35:49,356
What do you mean?

477
00:35:50,482 --> 00:35:52,525
No, no, no! Honestly, no.

478
00:35:53,902 --> 00:35:54,944
Yes, that's my ship.

479
00:35:55,612 --> 00:35:58,698
(SQUEALING)

480
00:35:58,782 --> 00:35:59,824
That's not true!

481
00:35:59,908 --> 00:36:03,453
I should know, I was there.
I fought in the war. It wasn't my fault.

482
00:36:04,496 --> 00:36:07,290
I couldn't save your world.
I couldn't save any of them.

483
00:36:09,334 --> 00:36:11,002
-What's it doing?
-It's the Tardis.

484
00:36:11,836 --> 00:36:15,507
The Nestene's identified it
as superior technology. It's terrified!

485
00:36:15,799 --> 00:36:17,092
It's going to the final base.

486
00:36:18,218 --> 00:36:21,304
It's starting the invasion.
Get out, Rose! Just leg it, now!

487
00:36:21,513 --> 00:36:23,014
(CONTINUES SQUEALING)

488
00:36:24,432 --> 00:36:27,227
-Mum?
-There you are! I was just gonna phone.

489
00:36:27,477 --> 00:36:30,146
You can get compensation,
I said so.

490
00:36:30,230 --> 00:36:32,691
I've got this document
thing off the police, don't thank me...

491
00:36:32,816 --> 00:36:35,443
-Where are you, Mum?
-I'm in town.

492
00:36:35,527 --> 00:36:37,612
Look, just go home!
Just go home right now.

493
00:36:37,696 --> 00:36:41,199
Darling, you're breaking up. I'm just
gonna do a bit of late night shopping

494
00:36:41,282 --> 00:36:43,076
I'll see you later. Ta-ra!

495
00:36:43,493 --> 00:36:44,994
Mum? Mum?

496
00:36:51,251 --> 00:36:54,129
It's the activation signal!
It's transmitting.

497
00:37:00,677 --> 00:37:02,303
It's the end of the world.

498
00:37:11,396 --> 00:37:12,731
There's no point
creating a spreadsheet

499
00:37:12,814 --> 00:37:14,607
if you're gonna spend
summer money in winter months.

500
00:37:14,691 --> 00:37:17,944
(GASPS) Oh, my God!
I thought they were dummies!

501
00:37:18,027 --> 00:37:19,529
I nearly had a heart attack.

502
00:37:33,752 --> 00:37:34,878
(GLASS SHATTERING)

503
00:37:47,015 --> 00:37:48,057
It's true.

504
00:37:48,141 --> 00:37:50,351
Everything I've read,
all those stories, it's all true!

505
00:37:55,440 --> 00:37:56,483
(SCREAMING)

506
00:37:56,566 --> 00:37:58,026
(SQUEALING)

507
00:37:59,402 --> 00:38:02,447
Get out, Rose! Just get out!
Run!

508
00:38:03,281 --> 00:38:04,574
ROSE: The stairs have gone.

509
00:38:10,205 --> 00:38:11,414
I haven't got the key.

510
00:38:14,501 --> 00:38:15,752
MICKEY: We're gonna die!

511
00:38:17,504 --> 00:38:19,380
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

512
00:38:36,439 --> 00:38:37,482
(GRUNTING)

513
00:38:47,367 --> 00:38:48,952
(SCREAMING)

514
00:38:49,327 --> 00:38:50,537
(CAR HONKING)

515
00:39:11,266 --> 00:39:12,559
(SCREAMS)

516
00:39:15,687 --> 00:39:18,231
NESTENE: Time Lord!

517
00:39:38,960 --> 00:39:40,044
Leave him!

518
00:39:47,802 --> 00:39:48,845
There's nothing you can do!

519
00:39:50,305 --> 00:39:51,806
I've got no A-levels.

520
00:39:53,141 --> 00:39:54,183
No job.

521
00:39:54,851 --> 00:39:55,894
No future.

522
00:39:57,478 --> 00:39:58,813
But I'll tell you what I have got.

523
00:39:59,606 --> 00:40:02,859
Jericho Street Junior School
under-sevens gymnastics team.

524
00:40:03,610 --> 00:40:04,777
I got the bronze!

525
00:40:05,904 --> 00:40:06,946
(GRUNTS)

526
00:40:16,539 --> 00:40:17,832
(SQUEALING)

527
00:40:19,334 --> 00:40:20,501
Rose!

528
00:40:24,172 --> 00:40:25,798
Now we're in trouble!

529
00:40:34,349 --> 00:40:36,434
(ALARM BELL RINGING)

530
00:41:01,960 --> 00:41:03,836
(TARDIS WHOOSHING)

531
00:41:46,170 --> 00:41:47,213
(MAN COUGHING)

532
00:41:47,547 --> 00:41:49,215
(WOMAN SOBBING)

533
00:41:53,302 --> 00:41:55,471
(SIREN WAILING
IN THE DISTANCE)

534
00:42:00,810 --> 00:42:02,145
(MOBILE PHONE RINGING)

535
00:42:04,939 --> 00:42:07,650
Rose, don't go out
of the house, it's not safe!

536
00:42:08,609 --> 00:42:11,696
There are these things,
they were shooting and...

537
00:42:11,988 --> 00:42:13,865
Hello? Hello?

538
00:42:18,661 --> 00:42:20,121
Fat lot of good you were!

539
00:42:21,080 --> 00:42:22,206
(WHIMPERING)

540
00:42:23,332 --> 00:42:25,877
Nestene Consciousness?
Easy!

541
00:42:26,377 --> 00:42:28,880
You were useless in there!
You'd be dead if it wasn't for me.

542
00:42:29,464 --> 00:42:30,506
Yes, I would.

543
00:42:31,799 --> 00:42:32,884
Thank you.

544
00:42:33,718 --> 00:42:35,344
Right, then! I'll be off.

545
00:42:36,471 --> 00:42:38,181
Unless... I don't know.

546
00:42:39,307 --> 00:42:40,600
You could come with me.

547
00:42:42,101 --> 00:42:43,770
This box isn't just
a London-op, you know,

548
00:42:43,853 --> 00:42:44,896
it goes anywhere
in the universe.

549
00:42:44,979 --> 00:42:46,147
Free of charge.

550
00:42:46,230 --> 00:42:49,192
Don't! He's an alien.
He's a thing.

551
00:42:49,776 --> 00:42:50,985
He's not invited.

552
00:42:52,195 --> 00:42:53,237
What do you think?

553
00:42:55,448 --> 00:42:56,783
You could stay here.

554
00:42:56,866 --> 00:43:00,161
Fill your life with work
and food and sleep, or you could go...

555
00:43:01,412 --> 00:43:02,455
Anywhere.

556
00:43:03,331 --> 00:43:05,291
-Is it always this dangerous?
-Yeah.

557
00:43:07,460 --> 00:43:09,212
Yeah, I can't.

558
00:43:10,129 --> 00:43:12,298
I've gotta go and
find my mum,

559
00:43:12,965 --> 00:43:15,593
and someone's gotta look after
this stupid lump, so...

560
00:43:18,346 --> 00:43:19,680
Okay.

561
00:43:21,307 --> 00:43:22,558
See you around.

562
00:43:33,528 --> 00:43:35,071
(TARDIS WHOOSHING)

563
00:43:56,008 --> 00:43:57,051
Come on, let's go.

564
00:43:58,386 --> 00:44:00,429
Come on. Come on.

565
00:44:07,562 --> 00:44:08,980
(TARDIS WHOOSHING)

566
00:44:17,780 --> 00:44:20,741
By the way, did I mention
it also travels in time?

567
00:44:26,205 --> 00:44:27,707
-Thanks.
-Thanks for what?

568
00:44:29,125 --> 00:44:30,168
Exactly.

569
00:44:42,680 --> 00:44:44,765
This is the year five billion,

570
00:44:45,516 --> 00:44:47,727
and this is the day...
Hold on...

571
00:44:50,980 --> 00:44:53,065
Welcome to
the end of the world.

572
00:44:53,482 --> 00:44:54,525
Who the hell are you?

573
00:44:55,234 --> 00:44:57,361
Oh, I'm the Doctor,
this is Rose Tyler.

574
00:44:57,445 --> 00:44:59,155
She's my plus one,
is that all right?

575
00:44:59,238 --> 00:45:01,407
Representing
the Forest of Cheam,

576
00:45:01,490 --> 00:45:05,661
we have Trees,
the Moxx of Balhoon,

577
00:45:05,745 --> 00:45:12,043
the Face of Boe, the last human,
the Lady Cassandra O'Brien.

578
00:45:12,376 --> 00:45:15,671
Oh, now, don't stare,
look how thin I am.

579
00:45:19,133 --> 00:45:20,134
That's not supposed to happen.

